Please confirm if Special Immigrant Juvenile Status (SISJ) is applicable for my case.

November 30, -0001 at 12:00 am

The SSIJ Act is for minors–someone who has not yet attained the age of 21. Technically, you may have ordered the case terminated without prejudice so that you could bring a second SIJ application based on age. It would be advisable to contact an attorney as soon as possible, for there are statute of limitations issues for this type of petition.

November 30, -0001 at 12:00 am

A client, as a minor, was placed in an institution that was both certified and approved as a group home for homeless children and adolescents and the facility was approved by the court to provide rehabilitative care while an interstate custody case was pending. The child was placed in a group home designed specifically to house runaways, drug users and addicts without addresses and no parents. The investigative agency discovered the allegation in the abuse report originated from the shelter.
